
---


@startuml
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0

' Define classes with relevant attributes and relationships

class Resident {
    +String name
    +String streetAddress
    +String phoneNumber
    +String email (optional)
    +String itemDescription
}

class PickupRequest {
    +Date pickupDate
    +TimeWindow timeWindow (8:00 - 14:00)
    +Resident resident
    +List<Item> items
}

class Item {
    +String description
    +float weight
    +Dimension dimensions
    +ItemType type
}

enum ItemType {
    SECOND_HAND_ARTICLE
    NON_PERISHABLE_FOOD
}

class VolunteerDriver {
    +String name
    +Vehicle vehicle
    +Set<DayOfWeek> availableDays
}

class Vehicle {
    +int capacity (storage space)
    +Location location
}

class PickupRoute {
    +Date date
    +List<PickupRequest> pickups
    +VolunteerDriver driver
    +calculateRoute()
}

class DistributionCenter {
    +Location location
    +processSecondHandArticles()
    +notifyClients()
}

class FoodBank {
    +Location location
    +receiveNonPerishableFoods()
}

class Employee {
    +String name
    +DistributionCenter distributionCenter
    +inspectAndTagArticle(Item)
    +assignCategoryToItem(Item, Category)
}

class Category {
    +int id
    +String name (e.g., "Baby Clothing", "Microwave")
}

class Client {
    +String name
    +String homeAddress
    +Set<Category> preferredCategories
}

class DeliveryService {
    +deliverItem(Client, Item)
    +scheduleDelivery()
}

class RFIDTag {
    +UUID tagID
    +Item item
}

' Associations and Relationships

Resident --> PickupRequest : places
PickupRequest --> Item : contains
PickupRequest --> Resident : belongs to

VolunteerDriver --> PickupRoute : drives
VolunteerDriver --> Vehicle : owns

PickupRoute --> PickupRequest : includes
PickupRoute --> VolunteerDriver : assigned to
PickupRoute --> Vehicle : uses

Item --> ItemType : has type
Item --> RFIDTag : may have
RFIDTag --> Item : tags

Employee --> DistributionCenter : works at
Employee --> Item : inspects and tags
Employee --> Category : assigns
Item --> Category : categorized as

DistributionCenter --> FoodBank : sends non-perishables to
DistributionCenter --> Client : notifies
Client --> Category : prefers
Client --> DeliveryService : receives via

DeliveryService --> VolunteerDriver : uses
DeliveryService --> Client : delivers to
DeliveryService --> Item : delivers

FoodBank --> Item : receives non-perishables from

@enduml

---

### 📌 Notes:

- The `PickupRequest` represents a scheduled pickup made by a `Resident`.
- `Item` can be either a `SECOND_HAND_ARTICLE` or `NON_PERISHABLE_FOOD`, which determines its handling path.
- A `VolunteerDriver` manages a `Vehicle` and participates in `PickupRoute`s when available.
- An `Employee` processes `Item`s at the `DistributionCenter`, including tagging and categorizing.
- The `DistributionCenter` may offer a `DeliveryService` to clients who request it.
- The `Category` list is fixed and standardized across all H2S locations.

